Cancer prevention links

Study on gene mutations and how surveillance doesn't detect most cancers in time (2013):
http://cancerpreventionresearch.aacrjournals.org/content/early/2013/11/19/1940-6207.CAPR-13-0289.full.pdf

Study on how surveillance doesn't detect most cancers in time, suggests NSAIDS (2003):
https://www.hon.ch/OESO/books/Vol_6_Barrett_s_Esophagus/Articles/vol2/art117.html

Study suggests RFA is best for preventing Barrett's progression (2014):
http://www.gastro.org/guidelines/2014/3/5/barrett-s-esophagus#sec5

Study suggests surgery plus RFA (if Barrett's does not shrink post surgery) (2015):
http://www.refluxmedical.com/en/news/cancer-prevention-and-barretts-esophagus-anti-reflux-surgery-or-medical-therapy/

Study suggests surgery better than drugs, but does not eliminate risk (2015):
http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26501714

Study suggests RFA for LGD, HGD Barrett's and high-risk non-dysplastic, 80-90% reduction in cancer risk (2015):
http://download.springer.com/static/pdf/862/art%253A10.1007%252Fs10353-015-0362-4.pdf?originUrl=http%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10353-015-0362-4&token2=exp=1452212545~acl=%2Fstatic%2Fpdf%2F862%2Fart%25253A10.1007%25252Fs10353-015-0362-4.pdf%3ForiginUrl%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Flink.springer.com%252Farticle%252F10.1007%252Fs10353-015-0362-4*~hmac=a9e2cbc04254056ff54821b955f74dcb920cc2f9127bcd076914c3a192c6adb4

